== Events == * [[Reki-nin]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1238]] {{ill|May 8|ja|5月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The monk Jōkō began the construction of the great Buddha at Kōtoku-ji in Kamakura (the Kamakura Daibutsu). * [[Kangen]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1246]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Kamakura shogunate’s Shikken, {{ill|Hojo Tokiyori|ja|北条時頼|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, due to severe illness, was succeeded by his younger brother as the 5th Shikken. * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1633]] {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The shogunate under 【征夷大将軍】 {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} instructed his close aides, including {{ill|Matsudaira Nobutsuna|ja|松平信綱|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, to deliberate and decide on minor matters, laying the foundation for the office of the {{ill|Wakadoshiyori|ja|若年寄|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1854]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Russian envoy, Puchachin, visited Nagasaki for a second time following his previous arrival. == Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1841]] {{ill|May 13|ja|5月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fukuchi Ō Sakurachi|ja|福地桜痴|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Fukuchi Genichirō), a journalist and playwright (died [[1906]]). == Deaths ==
== Commemorations == * [[Mazu Tan]] – Also known as {{ill|Tianhou|ja|天后|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, commemorating the birth of the sea goddess Mazu who protects fishermen and seafarers. Mazu is believed to have been born during the Song Dynasty in Fujian; large festivals are held at Mazu and Tianhou temples throughout Fujian, Taiwan, Guangdong, Hong Kong, and Macau.
