{{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 23''' is the 23rd day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[Reki-nin]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1238]] {{ill|May 8|ja|5月8日|qq=}}) – The monk Jōkō began the construction of the great Buddha at Kōtoku-ji in Kamakura (the Kamakura Daibutsu). * [[Kangen]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1246]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日|qq=}}) – The Kamakura shogunate’s Shikken, {{ill|Hojo Tokiyori|ja|北条時頼|qq=}}, due to severe illness, was succeeded by his younger brother as the 5th Shikken. * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1633]] {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|qq=}}) – The shogunate under 【征夷大将軍】 {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|qq=}} instructed his close aides, including {{ill|Matsudaira Nobutsuna|ja|松平信綱|qq=}}, to deliberate and decide on minor matters, laying the foundation for the office of the {{ill|Wakadoshiyori|ja|若年寄|qq=}}. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1854]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|qq=}}) – The Russian envoy, Puchachin, visited Nagasaki for a second time following his previous arrival. == Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1841]] {{ill|May 13|ja|5月13日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Fukuchi Ō Sakurachi|ja|福地桜痴|qq=}} (Fukuchi Genichirō), a journalist and playwright (died [[1906]]). == Deaths ==
