* [[Mazu Tan]] – Also known as {{ill|Tianhou|ja|天后|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, commemorating the birth of the sea goddess Mazu who protects fishermen and seafarers. Mazu is believed to have been born during the Song Dynasty in Fujian; large festivals are held at Mazu and Tianhou temples throughout Fujian, Taiwan, Guangdong, Hong Kong, and Macau.


