{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿三|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 23일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 23''' is the 23rd day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * [[Reki-nin]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1238]] {{ill|May 8|ja|5月8日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The monk Jōkō began the construction of the great Buddha at Kōtoku-ji in Kamakura (the Kamakura Daibutsu). * [[Kangen]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1246]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Kamakura shogunate’s Shikken, {{ill|Hojo Tokiyori|ja|北条時頼|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, due to severe illness, was succeeded by his younger brother as the 5th Shikken. * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1633]] {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The shogunate under 【征夷大将軍】 {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} instructed his close aides, including {{ill|Matsudaira Nobutsuna|ja|松平信綱|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, to deliberate and decide on minor matters, laying the foundation for the office of the {{ill|Wakadoshiyori|ja|若年寄|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1854]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Russian envoy, Puchachin, visited Nagasaki for a second time following his previous arrival. == Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1841]] {{ill|May 13|ja|5月13日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fukuchi Ō Sakurachi|ja|福地桜痴|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} (Fukuchi Genichirō), a journalist and playwright (died [[1906]]). == Deaths ==
== Commemorations == * [[Mazu Tan]] – Also known as {{ill|Tianhou|ja|天后|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, commemorating the birth of the sea goddess Mazu who protects fishermen and seafarers. Mazu is believed to have been born during the Song Dynasty in Fujian; large festivals are held at Mazu and Tianhou temples throughout Fujian, Taiwan, Guangdong, Hong Kong, and Macau.
