ted his close aides, including {{ill|Matsudaira Nobutsuna|ja|松平信綱|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Nobutsuna|qq=}}, to deliberate and decide on minor matters, laying the foundation for the office of the {{ill|Wakadoshiyori|ja|若年寄|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakadoshiyori|qq=}}. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ansei|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} [[1854]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/April 20|qq=}}) – The Russian envoy, Puchachin, visited Nagasaki for a second time following his previous arrival. == Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpō|qq=}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} [[1841]] {{ill|May 13|ja|5月13日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May 13|qq=}}) – {{ill|Fukuchi Ō Sakurachi|ja|福地桜痴|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuchi Ō Sakurachi|qq=}} (Fukuchi Genichirō), a journalist and playwright (died [[1906]]). == Deaths ==
== Commemorations == * [[Mazu Tan]] – Also known as {{ill|Tianhou|ja|天后|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tianhou|qq=}}, commemorating the birth of the sea goddess Mazu who protects fishermen and seafarers. Mazu is believed to have been born during the Song Dynasty in Fujian; large festivals are held at Mazu and Tianhou temples throughout Fujian, Taiwan, Guangdong, Hong Kong, and Macau.
