{{Not to be confused with|March 23 (Lunisolar)}}<!--hatnote--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿三|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 23일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 23''' is the 23rd day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[Reki-nin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1238]] [[:en:May 8|May 8]]) – The monk Jōkō began the construction of the great Buddha at Kōtoku-ji in Kamakura (the Kamakura Daibutsu). * [[Kangen]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1246]] [[:en:April 10|April 10]]) – The Kamakura shogunate’s Shikken, [[:en:Hōjō Tokiyori|Hojo Tokiyori]], due to severe illness, was succeeded by his younger brother as the 5th Shikken. * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1633]] [[:en:May 1|May 1]]) – The shogunate under 【征夷大将軍】 [[:en:Tokugawa Iemitsu|Tokugawa Iemitsu]] instructed his close aides, including [[:en:Matsudaira Nobutsuna|Matsudaira Nobutsuna]], to deliberate and decide on minor matters, laying the foundation for the office of the [[:en:Wakadoshiyori|Wakadoshiyori]]. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1854]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – The Russian envoy, Puchachin, visited Nagasaki for a second time following his previous arrival. == Births == * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1841]] [[:en:May 13|May 13]]) – {{ill|Fukuchi Ō Sakurachi|ja|福地桜痴|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuchi Ō Sakurachi|qq=}} (Fukuchi Genichirō), a journalist and playwright (died [[1906]]). == Deaths ==
== Commemorations == * [[Mazu Tan]] – Also known as [[:en:Tin Hau (disambiguation)|Tianhou]], commemorating the birth of the sea goddess Mazu who protects fishermen and seafarers. Mazu is believed to have been born during the Song Dynasty in Fujian; large festivals are held at Mazu and Tianhou temples throughout Fujian, Taiwan, Guangdong, Hong Kong, and Macau.
